<article>
    <h1>10 stores to get Christ&#xAD;mas finery</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201205/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-05"><time>2020-12-05</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | DESIGN</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>From ar­ti­sanal glass baubles to dis­counted tree trim­mings, get your Christ­mas trees and trim­mings at the fol­low­ing stores.</p>
    <p>Metro</p>
    <p>Be­sides tree trim­mings, Metro Christ­mas Magic, which is the store’s sig­na­ture fes­tive theme, fea­tures an ar­ray of home fra­grances from about $8 to ar­ti­fi­cial flow­ers and plants that start at about $80. Where: Metro Paragon at 02-28 Paragon, 290 Or­chard Road and Metro Cause­way Point at 01-18/19 Cause­way Point, 1 Wood­lands Square. Go to www.metro.com.sg</p>
    <p>Tangs Christ­mas Shop</p>
    <p>It is a Christ­mas won­der­land on Level 3 of Tang Plaza with ev­ery­thing from ar­ti­fi­cial trees and fes­tive tree dec­o­ra­tions to Christ­mas ham­pers and par­ty­ware, start­ing from $46 for a Pollyanna Ski Boy or­na­ment.</p>
    <p>Where: Tangs at Tang Plaza, Level 3, 310 Or­chard Road till Dec 27; Tangs VivoCity, Level 1 at 1 Har­bourfront Walk and Tangs.com till Dec 28. Go to www.tangs.com</p>
    <p>Ikea</p>
    <p>This year, Ikea fea­tures a range of re­al­is­tic-look­ing ar­ti­fi­cial Christ­mas trees in jute pot­ters. There is also a range of Swedish-style Christ­mas or­na­ments start­ing from about $3 for poin­set­tias. Where: Ikea at 317 Alexan­dra Road and 60 Tampines North Drive 2. Go to www.ikea.com.sg</p>
    <p>Daiso</p>
    <p>The Ja­panese dis­count store sells fes­tive decor at $2 a pop and you can get ev­ery­thing from mini Christ­mas trees to tin­sel and glit­ter at bar­gain-base­ment prices. Their white baubles are es­pe­cially en­chant­ing.</p>
    <p>Where: For its 20 store lo­ca­tions, go to www.daisosin­ga­pore.com.sg</p>
    <p>Spot­light</p>
    <p>Get craft ma­te­rial for chil­dren to make their own Christ­mas or­na­ments or go for in­ex­pen­sive tree trim­mings that start at about $6 for a pack of 30 metal­lic mini­baubles.</p>
    <p>Where: Spot­light, Level 5, Plaza Sin­ga­pura, 68 Or­chard Road and West­gate, Level 3, 3 Gate­way Drive. Go to www.spot­light.com.sg</p>
    <p>Strange & Deranged The lux­ury home decor store presents its an­nual Christ­mas col­lec­tion with a red and gold theme at its new flag­ship in Paragon. Find mouth­blown glass baubles with in­tri­cate l ace mo­tifs and vin­tage in­spired or­na­ments from the 1930s from Es­to­nia and other parts of Europe. A hand-painted glass drop (above) costs $33.</p>
    <p>Where: Strange & Deranged at 04-47 Paragon, 290 Or­chard Road. Go to www.strange­an­deranged.com</p>
    <p>Ma­sons Home Decor</p>
    <p>Can­not find a real tree? Head to Ma­sons for syn­thetic Christ­mas trees that look al­most like the real thing. Its trees are sell­ing out fast, so try to get an early start. From $119 for an ar­ti­fi­cial pine tree. Where: Ma­sons Home Decor, 03-01C, 39A Jalan Pemimpin. Go to www.ma­son.com.sg</p>
    <p>Lim Hock Swee</p>
    <p>Get Christ­mas gar­lands, LED lights and tin­sel sta­ples at this fes­tive favourite along Gey­lang Road. Prices start at be­low $10.</p>
    <p>Where: 801 Gey­lang Road</p>
    <p>Sin­ga­pore Trad­ing Post</p>
    <p>Get pineapple lights for $38 and a star-shaped ta­ble or­na­ment for $85 at this eclec­tic gifts and home decor store.</p>
    <p>Where: For store lo­ca­tions, go to www.sin­ga­pore­trad­ing­post.com</p>
    <p>Vanda Win</p>
    <p>The home ac­ces­sories shop has stopped tak­ing or­ders on­line for its fast-sell­ing ar­ti­fi­cial Christ­mas trees and is now sell­ing them only at its phys­i­cal store. Choose from a wide range of tree or­na­ments, gar­lands, wreaths, rib­bons and fes­tive flora such as poin­set­tias.</p>
    <p>Where: Vanda Win, 03-25/26/27 Kinex, 11 Tan­jong Ka­tong Road</p>

